glosses: to leave, exit, quit, get out

examples.text: Hayatı asla ciddiye alma, zaten canlı çıkan yok.
examples.translation: Never take life seriously. Nobody gets out alive anyway.
You are no longer a child, you have become a young man.

examples.text: Evde çok kalıyorsun. Daha sık dışarı çık.
examples.translation: You stay home too much. Get out more often.
Motor oil stain gets out hard.

examples.text: Savaş bu küçük şehir yüzünden çıktı.
examples.translation: The war occurred because of this small city.
The child climbed the tree without thinking.
I've been dating Ercan for two years.
Subtracting six from ten equals four.

glosses: to appear, to look (on a photo, video, etc.)

examples.text: Çok kötü çıkmışım, bir daha çek.
examples.translation: I look so bad, take another photo.

examples.text: Kalan undan ancak iki kaşık çıkar.
examples.translation: The remaining flour will only make two spoons.
This street leads to the coast.

glosses: to turn out; to become apparent or known

examples.translation: The man turned out to be competent.
This newspaper is published once a week.
S(he) appeared as the lead role in the new play.

glosses: to go out for an activity

examples.translation: Let's go for a run tomorrow.

etymology:
From Ottoman Turkish چیقمق, from Proto-Turkic *čïk- (“to go out”).
